{
  "id": "dummy",
  "name": "Dummy Deck",
  "description": "Sandbox for testing new technical phrases before migration.",
  "deckType": "flippable",
  "cards": [
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_001",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Siento que no me hacen mucho caso.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "I feel like I'm not being listened to much.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_001_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I feel like they're not paying much attention to me.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_001_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I feel like I'm being mostly ignored.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_001_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I feel like they are ignoring me.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_001_sideB_3.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I feel like I'm being ignored.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_001_sideB_4.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_002",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Siento que no me hacen caso.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "I feel like I'm being ignored.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_002_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I feel like they aren't listening to me.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_002_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I feel like I'm not being heard.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_002_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_003",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Así respetamos el valor configurado en el perfil.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "That way, we respect the value configured in the profile.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_003_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "This ensures we keep the value set in the profile.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_003_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "This way we honor the profile's configured value.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_003_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "That way, we respect the configured value in the profile.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_003_sideB_3.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_004",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Osea, tu dices cero no?",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "So, you mean zero, right?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_004_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I mean, you're saying zero, correct?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_004_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "In other words, you mean zero, right?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_004_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "~So, you say zero, right?~ is unnatural in this context. [Say] refers to the physical act of speaking, while [mean] refers to the intention or meaning behind the words (querer decir).\n\n~So, you mean zero, no?~ and ~So, you mean zero, not?~ are incorrect. English does not use [no] or [not] as a question tag at the end of a sentence. You must use [right], [correct], or a proper question tag."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_005",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Eso define los privilegios del rol usuario.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "That defines the privileges of the user role.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_005_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "That determines the user role's privileges.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_005_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "This sets the privileges for the user role.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_005_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_006",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "No conozco el alcance de sus privilegios.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "I don't know the scope of their privileges.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_006_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I'm not aware of the extent of their privileges.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_006_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I don't know how far their privileges extend.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_006_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_007",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Prefiero no pensar acerca de ello.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "I prefer not to think about it.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_007_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I'd rather not think about it.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_007_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I'd prefer not to dwell on it.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_007_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_008",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "¿Quieres que te hable acerca de lo que hice?",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "Do you want me to talk about what I did?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_008_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Would you like me to tell you about what I did?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_008_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Should I go over what I've done?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_008_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_009",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "¿Quieres que te hable acerca de como debería ser?",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "Do you want me to talk about how it should be?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_009_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Would you like me to explain how it's supposed to be?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_009_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Should I go over how it ought to be?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_009_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_010",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "¿Quieres que te hable acerca de como debería funcionar?",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "Do you want me to talk about how it should work?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_010_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Would you like me to explain how it's supposed to work?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_010_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Should I discuss how it should function?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_010_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_011",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "¿Quieres que te hable acerca de lo que haré?",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "Do you want me to talk about what I'll do?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_011_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Would you like me to tell you what I'm going to do?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_011_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Should I explain my next steps?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_011_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_012",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Cualquier persona puede hacer eso.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "Anyone can do that.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_012_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Anybody is able to do that.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_012_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "That's something anyone can do.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_012_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_013",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Nadie puede hacer eso acá.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "No one can do that here.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_013_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Nobody can do that around here.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_013_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "No one is able to do that here.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_013_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_014",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Algunas personas pueden hacerlo.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "Some people can do it.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_014_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "A few people are able to do that.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_014_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "There are some people who can do it.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_014_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_015",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Dependeremos de eso. / Nos basaremos en eso.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "We will rely upon that.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_015_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "We'll depend upon that.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_015_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "That is what we will rely upon.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_015_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "We will rely on that.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_015_sideB_3.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "We will depend on that.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_015_sideB_4.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "We are going to rely on that.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_015_sideB_5.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "Upon is simply a more formal and elevated version of the preposition [on]. In modern conversational English, [on] is much more common."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_016",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Debe estar declarado a nivel de clase.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "It must be declared at the class level.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_016_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "It should be declared at the class level.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_016_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "It has to be declared at the class level.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_016_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "**[87]**\n\n~It must be declared in a level class~ is incorrect because the compound noun is [class level] (the level of the class), and we use the preposition [at] for this context: [at the class level]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_017",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Debe estar declarado en la zona declarativa.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "It must be declared in the declarative section.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_017_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "It should be declared in the declarative zone.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_017_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "It has to be in the declarative area.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_017_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_018",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "OK, le daré un vistazo a ese.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "OK, I'll take a look at that one.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_018_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Alright, I'll give that one a look.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_018_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "OK, I will look into that one.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_018_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "~OK, I'll take a look on that~ is incorrect because the phrase is [take a look at]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_019",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "En los pricing details puedes ver los diferentes ajustes que ha recibido.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "In the pricing details, you can see the different adjustments it has received.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_019_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "You can see the various adjustments it got in the pricing details.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_019_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "The pricing details show the different adjustments it's had.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_019_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_020",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Puedes ver el botón en la parte izquierda de abajo.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "You can see the button in the bottom left.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_020_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "The button is visible in the bottom left corner.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_020_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "You'll find the button at the bottom left.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_020_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "**[153]**\n\n~You can see the button in the left bottom.~ is not natural. In English, vertical positions ([top], [bottom]) always precede horizontal positions ([left], [right]), so it must be [bottom left]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_021",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Puedes ver el botón en la parte derecha de arriba.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "You can see the button in the top right.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_021_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "The button is visible in the top right corner.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_021_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "You'll find the button at the top right.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_021_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "You can see the button at the top right.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_021_sideB_3.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "**[153]**\n\n~You can see the button in the up right.~ is incorrect because we use the adjective [top] for the highest position, not the directional adverb [up]. Use [top right]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_022",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "La opción esta en la parte de abajo.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "The option is at the bottom.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_022_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "The option is down at the bottom.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_022_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "You'll find the option at the bottom.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_022_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "**[153]**\n\n~The option is at the below~ is incorrect because [below] is a preposition or adverb, not a noun. You must use [at the bottom]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_023",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "La opción esta en la parte de arriba.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "The option is at the top.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_023_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "The option is up at the top.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_023_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "You'll find the option at the top.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_023_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "**[153]**\n\n~The option is at the up.~ is incorrect because [up] is a direction, not a noun. The correct noun for the highest point is [the top].\n\n~The option is up.~ is incorrect in this context because [is up] usually means a system is functioning or refers to a general upward direction, not a specific location on a screen."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_024",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Son pocos problemas, podemos resolverlos pronto.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "There are only a few issues; we can resolve them soon.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_024_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "It's just a few problems, we can fix them quickly.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_024_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "They are minor issues, we can solve them shortly.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_024_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "**[105]**\n\n~There are only a litte bit issues; we can resolve them soon.~ is not valid because [issues] is a countable noun. You must use [a few] for countable nouns. [A little bit] is used with uncountable nouns."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_025",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "El día que se hizo el pedido de los productos.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "The day the products were ordered.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_025_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "The day the product order was placed.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_025_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "The day the order for the products was made.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_025_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "~The day the order of the products was made.~ is not the most natural choice. We typically use the preposition [for] with [order] when specifying items, or we use a compound noun like [product order].\n\n~The day the purchase for the products was made.~ is incorrect because [pedido] translates to [order], not [purchase]. Additionally, [purchase] refers to the transaction, while [order] refers to the request for the items."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_026",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "El día que se hizo la compra.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "The day the purchase was made.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_026_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "The day the purchase took place.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_026_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "The date of the purchase.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_026_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "The day the order was made.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_026_sideB_3.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "**[18]**\n\nPurchase refers to the act of buying something or the item bought (compra).\n\n~The order day~ is less natural. We usually say [the day of the order].\n\n~The day the purchase was done.~ is incorrect because the collocation is to [make] a purchase, not to [do] a purchase. Use [was made]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_027",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "El día que se hará la compra.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "The day the purchase will be made.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_027_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "The day the purchase is going to be made.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_027_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "The date the purchase will take place.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_027_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "**[18]**\n\n[Purchase] (noun) translates to 'compra' or 'adquisición'. It refers to the act of buying something.\n\n~The day the order will be made.~ is not an exact translation because [order] means 'pedido', while [purchase] means 'compra'.\n\n~The day the purchase will be done.~ is incorrect because we [make] a purchase, we do not [do] it. Use [will be made]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_028",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Existe una configuración desconocida.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "There is an unknown configuration.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_028_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "An unknown setting exists.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_028_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "There's an unrecognized configuration.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_028_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "~There is an undiscovered configuration.~ is not the best fit. [Undiscovered] implies something hidden that hasn't been found yet, whereas [unknown] means it is not recognized or identified by the system."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_029",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Existe alguna layer desconocida.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "There is some unknown layer.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_029_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Some unknown layer exists.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_029_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "There's an unrecognized layer.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_029_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "There is an unknown layer.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_029_sideB_3.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "There is some undiscovered layer.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_029_sideB_4.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "~It exists some unknown layer~ is incorrect because [exist] cannot be used with a dummy 'it' followed by a noun. Use [There is] or make the noun the subject: [Some unknown layer exists]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_030",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Escucho todo el día inglés, cosas como podcast, o videos random.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "I listen to English all day, things like podcasts or random videos.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_030_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I hear English all day long, like podcasts or random videos.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_030_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I spend all day listening to English through podcasts and random videos.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_030_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_031",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Pero no son retrocesos, son problemas no descubiertos.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "But they aren't regressions; they are undiscovered issues.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_031_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "They are not regressions, they are just unfound problems.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_031_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "They're not steps back, they're undiscovered issues.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_031_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "They're not setbacks, they're undiscovered issues.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_031_sideB_3.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "They're not steps back, they're unknown issues.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_031_sideB_4.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "~They're not stepbacks, they're undiscovered issues.~ is not valid because [stepbacks] is not a standard word. The correct noun is [setbacks] or the phrase [steps back]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_032",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "No es un retroceso, es un nuevo problema descubierto.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "It's not a regression; it's a newly discovered issue.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_032_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "It isn't a regression, it's a new problem we found.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_032_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "That's not a regression, it's just a newly found bug.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_032_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "It's not a setback; it's a newly discovered issue.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_032_sideB_3.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "~It's not a regression; it's new discovered issue~ is missing the article [a] and the adverb form [newly] to modify the adjective 'discovered'.\n\n~It's not a setback; it's a new discovered issue.~ is incorrect because the adjective 'discovered' must be modified by an adverb [newly], not another adjective [new].\n\n~It's not a setback; it's an undiscovered issue.~ changes the meaning. [Undiscovered] means it has NOT been found yet, whereas the Spanish sentence states it IS a newly [discovered] problem."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_033",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Esperamos tener un sistema híbrido.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "We expect to have a hybrid system.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_033_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "We're hoping for a hybrid system.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_033_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "We hope to have a hybrid setup.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_033_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "We're expecting to have a hybrid system.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_033_sideB_3.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_034",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "El update popup será híbrido.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "The update popup will be hybrid.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_034_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
