    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_035",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Necesitaremos subir el número de versión en el profile.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "We'll need to bump the version number in the profile.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_035_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "We will need to increase the version number in the profile.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_035_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "We'll have to bump up the version in the profile.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_035_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "~We'll need to increase the number of the version in the profile.~ sounds unnatural. We use the compound noun [version number] instead of connecting them with [of]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_036",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Debemos subir la version en el profile en cada release.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "We must bump the version in the profile for every release.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_036_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "We need to increase the version in the profile on each release.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_036_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "We have to bump up the version in the profile with every release.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_036_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "We need to increase the version in the profile for each release.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_036_sideB_3.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "~We need to go up the version in the profile on each release.~ is not valid because [go up] is intransitive and cannot take a direct object. You must use a transitive verb like [increase], [raise], or [bump]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_037",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Debe ser un trabajo coordinado.",
      "sideB": [
