    {
      "cardId": "dummy_038",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "¿Está bien dicho?",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "Is that said correctly?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_038_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Is that the right way to say it?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_038_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Did I say that right?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_038_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Did I say it right?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_038_sideB_3.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "\n\n~Is it said right?~ is grammatically awkward. In the passive voice, it is much more natural to use the adverb [correctly] instead of the colloquial [right]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_039",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "¿Lo dije bien?",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "Did I say it right?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_039_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Did I say it correctly?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_039_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Was that said properly?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_039_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "~Did I say it well?~ sounds unnatural for asking about accuracy or pronunciation. [Well] usually refers to the quality of the performance or eloquence, whereas [right] or [correctly] refers to accuracy."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_040",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "No sé para qué es esto.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "I don't know what this is for.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_040_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I have no idea what this is for.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_040_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I'm not sure what this is used for.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_040_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "**[111]**"
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_041",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "No sé para qué es eso.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "I don't know what that is for.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_041_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I have no idea what that is for.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_041_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "I'm not sure what that is used for.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_041_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "**[111]**\n\n**[148]**\n\n~I don't know what that used is for~ has incorrect word order. The passive voice structure requires the verb to be before the past participle: [what that is used for].\n\n~I don't know what is that for.~ is incorrect because embedded questions must follow standard statement word order (Subject + Verb), without inversion. It should be [what that is]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_042",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "¿Qué parte demora más en cargar?",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "Which part takes the longest to load?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_042_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "What part takes more time to load?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_042_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Which part takes longer to load?",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_042_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_043",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Las Cuentas por Cobrar son el dinero que los clientes deben a la empresa.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "Accounts Receivable is the money that customers owe to the company.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_043_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Accounts Receivable represents the money clients owe the company.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_043_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Accounts Receivable are the funds owed to the business by its customers.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_043_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_044",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Las Cuentas por Cobrar gestionan los límites de crédito de los clientes.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "Accounts Receivable manages the credit limits of the customers.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_044_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Accounts Receivable handles customer credit limits.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_044_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Accounts Receivable controls the credit limits for clients.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_044_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "The word [Receivable] literally means \"able to be received.\" In finance and accounting, it refers to money that a business has the right to receive because it has provided a product or service. Therefore, \"Accounts Receivable\" translates to \"Cuentas por cobrar\"."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_045",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Las Cuentas por Cobrar se clasifican como un activo de la empresa.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "Accounts Receivable are classified as a company asset.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_045_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Accounts Receivable is categorized as an asset of the company.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_045_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "Accounts Receivable is considered a company asset.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_045_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "~Accounts Receivable are classified as an active for the company.~ is not valid because [active] is a false friend in this context. The financial term for 'activo' is [asset]."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_046",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Ha tomado tiempo.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "It has taken time.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_046_sideB_0.mp3"
